Why do I think that restricting is the only way for me to lose weight? I have never lost weight on purpose. Because every time I restrict, it ends up being a two week long binge. And I am too dumb to eat healthy and to look after how much calories I eat because I'll end up obsessing over calories and then not eating enough. I don't want to get long term health damages from not eating enough. I wish I would just lose fat without even realizing it. I am sick and tired of being insecure of my belly for almost 17 years now. Something HAS TO CHANGE NOW. It wouldn't even take long for me. I'm not super duper fat. Over quarantine even my face and my shoulders got fat. I feel so damn ugly. I don't know what to do
